pots of ointment... "

262
00:33:54,720 --> 00:33:58,872
Remember that picnic, Sister, last year,
when Western sat on a wasps' nest?

263
00:33:59,000 --> 00:34:00,956
I shall never forget it!

264
00:34:02,040 --> 00:34:05,794
Oh, it's so beautiful this summer.

265
00:34:08,480 --> 00:34:10,038
Brother... Brother...

266
00:34:10,160 --> 00:34:12,469
- Brother!
- Whoa! Whoa!

267
00:34:12,840 --> 00:34:15,559
- I can't...
- It's all right. It's all right.

268
00:34:46,000 --> 00:34:47,991
Why the long face, Blif?

269
00:34:48,120 --> 00:34:50,475
- Such a terrible thing.
- What's happened?

270
00:34:50,600 --> 00:34:53,592
There's been an accident.
My mother is dead.

271
00:34:57,280 --> 00:34:59,032
Blif...

272
00:35:01,080 --> 00:35:03,036
And Squire Allworthy?

273
00:35:03,920 --> 00:35:06,070
He's not expected to live.

274
00:35:09,800 --> 00:35:10,710
Shh.

275
00:35:10,840 --> 00:35:14,753
Fever has developed and there
is little hope. We can only pray.

276
00:35:15,400 --> 00:35:17,755
Something for which
you have scant relish!

277
00:35:18,640 --> 00:35:22,792
"Forasmuch as it hath pleased
Almighty God of his great mercy

278
00:35:22,920 --> 00:35:27,152
to take unto himself the soul
of our dear sister here departed,

279
00:35:27,280 --> 00:35:29,794
we therefore commit
her body to the ground,

280
00:35:29,920 --> 00:35:31,478
earth to earth,

281
00:35:31,600 --> 00:35:33,272
ashes to ashes,

282
00:35:33,400 --> 00:35:35,516
dust to dust,

283
00:35:35,640 --> 00:35:39,952
in sure and certain hope
of the resurrection to eternal life,

284
00:35:40,080 --> 00:35:44,119
through our Lord Jesus Christ. Amen. "

285
00:35:44,640 --> 00:35:46,870
Well, there's another one gone.

286
00:35:58,960 --> 00:36:00,916
So sorry.

287
00:36:01,560 --> 00:36:03,516
Cheer up, lad.

288
00:36:03,640 --> 00:36:05,551
She will be with the angels, my boy.

289
00:36:05,680 --> 00:36:09,036
Our mortal forms are but shadows
of a purer reality.

290
00:36:11,080 --> 00:36:15,278
- Thank you for your comforting words.
- She was a great lady.

291
00:36:16,920 --> 00:36:20,708
Sir, some time before your mother died
she gave me a letter.

292
00:36:20,840 --> 00:36:24,992
Her instructions were to hand it
to Mr Allworthy as she was buried.

293
00:36:25,120 --> 00:36:26,712
I will give it to my uncle.

294
00:36:26,840 --> 00:36:29,991
She expressly said
into no hands but Mr Allworthy's.

295
00:36:30,120 --> 00:36:34,352
Lawyer Dowling, if my uncle lives
he will need a new steward.

296
00:36:34,480 --> 00:36:36,675
I intend to recommend you.

297
00:36:36,800 --> 00:36:39,109
You are most kind, sir.

298
00:36:52,080 --> 00:36:56,995
Do not grieve, my dear nephew.
Do not grieve.

299
00:36:59,600 --> 00:37:01,556
Sir, you cannot die.

300
00:37:05,440 --> 00:37:08,079
Death comes to us all, Tom.

301
00:37:08,800 --> 00:37:12,554
I have asked you here
to tell you of my will.

302
00:37:13,280 --> 00:37:20,118
Nephew Blifil, I leave you heir to my
whole estate, with these exceptions.

303
00:37:23,560 --> 00:37:29,271
<i>To you, my dear Tom,
I have given an estate of Pounds. 800 a year,</i>

304
00:37:29,400 --> 00:37:32,517
<i>together with Pounds. 1,000 in ready money.</i>

305
00:37:33,160 --> 00:37:36,152
I am convinced, my boy,

306
00:37:36,280 --> 00:37:43,197
that you have much goodness,
generosity and honour in your nature.

307
00:37:43,320 --> 00:37:49,589
If you will add prudence and religion
to these, you must be happy.

308
00:37:53,920 --> 00:38:00,075
<i>Pounds. 1,000 I leave to you, Mr Thwackum,
and a like sum to you, Mr Square -</i>

309
00:38:00,200 --> 00:38:05,399
which I am convinced exceeds
your desires as well as your wants.

310
00:38:06,160 --> 00:38:10,438
<i>As for my servants,
for Marjorie and Jane, Pounds. 100 each.</i>

311
00:38:10,560 --> 00:38:13,552
"... my soul shall praise the Lord
even to death,

312
00:38:13,680 --> 00:38:16,148
and my life was drawing
near to hell beneath... "

313
00:38:16,280 --> 00:38:21,912
Mr Allworthy's recovered!

314
00:38:22,040 --> 00:38:24,190
It's over! The fever's gone!

315
00:38:24,320 --> 00:38:28,233
He's sitting up! He's well again!
The squire's recovered!

316
00:38:28,360 --> 00:38:30,396
It's over!

317
00:38:34,120 --> 00:38:37,795
<i>It is not true that drink
changes a man's character.</i>

318
00:38:38,680 --> 00:38:41,069
<i>It can reveal it more clearly.</i>

319
00:38:41,720 --> 00:38:46,430
<i>The Squire's recovery brought joy to Tom,
to his tutors sheer disappointment.</i>

320
00:38:46,560 --> 00:38:51,554
Sing, thick Thwackum,
your bounty's flown...

321
00:38:51,680 --> 00:38:55,355
You have good reason for your
drunkenness, you beggarly bastard!

322
00:38:55,480 --> 00:39:00,395
- He's provided well enough for you!
- Do you think that could weigh with me?

323
00:39:00,520 --> 00:39:03,318
- Damn you, Thwackum!
- How dare you, sir?!

324
00:39:03,440 --> 00:39:06,557
And damn me
if I don't open another bottle.

325
00:39:10,560 --> 00:39:15,315
I shall sing you a ballad, entitled "Sing,
thick Thwackum, thy bounty has flown".

326
00:39:15,440 --> 00:39:18,671
Sing, thick Thwackum,
thy bounty's flown

327
00:39:18,800 --> 00:39:22,190
You've lost all the money
you thought that you'd own...

328
00:39:22,320 --> 00:39:24,276
Mr Jones!

329
00:39:25,200 --> 00:39:29,318
This house is in mourning on account
of the death of my dear mother.

330
00:39:30,000 --> 00:39:33,072
Oh, sir, forgive me.
The joy of Mr Allworthy's recovery...

331
00:39:33,200 --> 00:39:36,749
I had the misfortune
to know who my parents were.

332
00:39:36,880 --> 00:39:39,440
Consequently, I'm grieved by their loss.

333
00:39:41,680 --> 00:39:44,274
You rascal. Do you dare to insult me?

334
00:39:44,880 --> 00:39:48,475
Gentlemen, gentlemen!
This behaviour is most unseemly.

335
00:39:54,160 --> 00:39:57,118
<i>Oh, Master Blifil!</i>

336
00:39:57,240 --> 00:40:00,755
Oh, that vulgar animal! Out with him!

337
00:40:01,440 --> 00:40:04,989
All right, we'll go outside!
Let's have some wine!

338
00:40:05,120 --> 00:40:07,350
Get him out! Get him out!

339
00:40:12,480 --> 00:40:14,630
How dare you throw me out?

340
00:40:16,760 --> 00:40:18,876
Shall we take the evening air?

341
00:40:21,200 --> 00:40:25,318
<i>It is widely held that too much wine
will dull a man's desire.</i>

342
00:40:26,240 --> 00:40:28,674
<i>Indeed it will - in a dull man.</i>

343
00:40:29,160 --> 00:40:31,515
Sophia...

344
00:40:35,760 --> 00:40:37,876
Sophie...

345
00:40:40,760 --> 00:40:44,799
I'll carve her name on this tree!

346
00:40:46,600 --> 00:40:51,674
Tree, do you mind
if I carve the name of my Sophia?

347
00:40:52,280 --> 00:40:55,590
Big S for Sophia... Sophie...

348
00:40:56,120 --> 00:40:58,350
Sophie, Sophia...

349
00:40:59,760 --> 00:41:01,716
So... Molly...

350
00:41:02,240 --> 00:41:07,234
Molly, Molly, Molly, Molly, Molly, Molly...
M for Molly...

351
00:41:08,320 --> 00:41:11,039
Are you aimin' to slit my throat, Squire?

352
00:41:11,960 --> 00:41:15,509
Would you like... a sip of my wine?

353
00:41:15,640 --> 00:41:16,789
Mm.

354
00:41:16,920 --> 00:41:20,390
I never had a sip
of a gentleman's wine before.

355
00:41:23,960 --> 00:41:26,190
Oh, it's very potent!

356
00:41:35,320 --> 00:41:37,709
What are you laughin' at, Tom?

357
00:41:39,200 --> 00:41:41,714
I'm thinking of Square in your bedroom!

358
00:41:47,120 --> 00:41:52,399
<i>To those who find our hero's behaviour
startling, the answer is simple.:</i>

359
00:41:52,520 --> 00:41:55,751
<i>Tom had always thought
that any woman was better than none,</i>

360
00:41:55,880 --> 00:41:59,668
<i>while Molly never felt that one man
was quite as good as two.</i>

361
00:42:00,960 --> 00:42:03,599
- He has a wench!
- A wench?

362
00:42:03,720 --> 00:42:06,359
- Let's go and find the wicked girl.
- Yes!

363
00:42:09,280 --> 00:42:11,191
Who's that?

364
00:42:21,840 --> 00:42:23,592
- How dare you?!
- Thwacky! Ha-ha!

365
00:42:23,720 --> 00:42:25,676
Mr Jones, control yourself!

366
00:42:27,000 --> 00:42:28,956
How disgraceful!

367
00:42:29,880 --> 00:42:31,757
Go away, sir! Go away, sir!

368
00:42:45,240 --> 00:42:47,151
Take that, you wicked fool!

369
00:42:48,000 --> 00:42:50,355
You there! Damnation to you!

370
00:42:50,480 --> 00:42:53,040
Stop it! Stop! What's the matter with you?

371
00:42:53,720 --> 00:42:56,075
Damnation to you! Get over there!

372
00:42:56,200 --> 00:42:58,919
Whoa, there! Three falling onto one?

373
00:42:59,040 --> 00:43:00,996
Whoa! The whip!

374
00:43:01,600 --> 00:43:05,593
Come, lass, see to Tom.
He's in a devilish pickle, I promise you.

375
00:43:07,520 --> 00:43:10,239
Tom... Shh. Poor Tom. Shh.

376
00:43:13,840 --> 00:43:17,230
- Sophie, dear...
- Shh. I'll fetch some water.

377
00:43:17,360 --> 00:43:21,194
- What are you brawling about, Tom?
- If you search the bushes you'll find out.

378
00:43:39,520 --> 00:43:41,636
You lickerish dog, you!

379
00:43:42,560 --> 00:43:47,873
Where is she? Where's Tom's pussy?
