a wanton harlot to justice!

387
00:44:10,680 --> 00:44:13,194
The fault lies with Mr Allworthy
and yourself, sir.

388
00:44:13,320 --> 00:44:15,629
If you would put
the right laws into execution,

389
00:44:15,760 --> 00:44:18,354
you would soon rid the country
of these... vermin.

390
00:44:18,480 --> 00:44:21,119
Ha! I'd sooner rid the country of foxes!

391
00:44:21,840 --> 00:44:25,389
Come, you sup with me. Damn me
if there's nothing I wouldn't give you -

392
00:44:25,520 --> 00:44:28,637
except my hounds
and my favourite mare, Miss Slouch.

393
00:44:29,120 --> 00:44:30,473
Up...

394
00:44:30,600 --> 00:44:32,556
Away, Miss Slouch!

395
00:44:38,080 --> 00:44:40,548
Let us tell Mr Allworthy
how the monster has behaved!

396
00:44:40,680 --> 00:44:43,433
No, sirs, I beg of you, let us wait.

397
00:44:44,560 --> 00:44:46,710
A better time will come.

398
00:44:51,120 --> 00:44:54,715
Odds zodikins, it's me sister's coach.
What brings her from London?

399
00:44:54,840 --> 00:44:57,354
I hope the old bitch has gone to bed.

400
00:45:01,320 --> 00:45:04,437
Come, Sophie, sing us
one of your jolly songs, my girl.

401
00:45:04,560 --> 00:45:07,074
Father, I do not feel well.
I think I shall go to bed.

402
00:45:07,200 --> 00:45:11,557
Not before you attend to your guest.
Tom here has a great thirst, I warrant you.

403
00:45:11,680 --> 00:45:15,070
Western? What are these nocturnal riots?

404
00:45:15,640 --> 00:45:18,029
- Now lookie here, Sister...
- Sophie?

405
00:45:18,160 --> 00:45:19,513
- Yes, Aunt?
- To bed.

406
00:45:19,640 --> 00:45:21,358
- Bed?
- Bed!

407
00:45:21,480 --> 00:45:23,436
